'''Stone chests''' are thievable chests in the [[Lizardman Temple]] that require level 64 [[Thieving]] to steal from. Each stone chest yields 280 [[experience]], and the chest's loot respawns instantly. These chests are the only non-combat method of obtaining a [[Xeric's talisman]].

Upon failing to loot a stone chest, there is a 1/8 chance to get teleported out of the Lizardman Temple.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1235135611067084800|date=4 March 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/ZkRYI|archivedate=30 May 2020|quote=[Assuming you fail thieving the stone chests in the Lizardman Temple, what's the probability of getting teleported out?] 1/8}} Carrying a [[lockpick]] in your inventory increases the rate at which you successfully pick the lock of these chests.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1194739316460797955|date=13 November 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/q3wps|archivedate=30 May 2020|quote=At level 99 your success chance is 60.4% without a lockpick, 70.2% with one. At level 50, it'd be about 19.2% and 29.0% respectively (though you'd still need level 64 to be allowed to try). Interpolate linearly between those.}}

In order to save inventory space when looting the chest, it is recommended to bring a [[gem bag]], [[seed box]] and possibly also a [[needle]] and [[thread]] to sew the commonly obtained [[Xerican fabric]]s on the spot. Alternatively, you may bring a chisel and fletch the sapphires and rubies into bolt tips, which can stack with bolt tips obtained from the chest. Additionally, you may also want to bring a spade and some teleportation methods if you intend to solve any looted clue scrolls as soon as you get them.

==Getting there==
Three stone chests can be found by the [[Shayzien Infiltrator]] in the Lizardman Temple.

There are multiple ways of accessing [[Molch]], with the village itself being located in the middle of the [[Kebos Lowlands]]. Some poison protection is recommended, since lizardmen near the entrance can poison you.

*Players can teleport to the [[Farming Guild]] with the use of a [[skills necklace]] and walk south-east. If one lacks the 45 farming requirement, this teleport will place the player outside the guild.
*Players with 99 Farming may use the [[Farming cape]] teleport and run south-east.
*Players can use the [[fairy ring]] {{fairycode|cir}} to teleport to the north of the Kebos Lowlands. This requires partial completion of [[Fairytale II - Cure a Queen]].
*Players on the [[Arceuus spellbook]] can cast [[Battlefront Teleport]], which teleports players north-east of Molch. Players who lack the required Magic level may use the [[Battlefront teleport (tablet)|magic tablet]] equivalent.

